                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am going to play devils advocate, just because that is my nature.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Only, in the last four expansions time and time again our abilities to effect the circumstances have been nerfed.
<br />

<br />
Quote:
<br />
Enchanters specialize on improving the minds of their allies, with unmatched mana regeneration spells and mental enhancements.
<br />

<br />

<br />
So many other classes have mana regen now, this is just plainly false. And that's without even taking into account that from 45th to 59th no group wants enchanter mind buffs in group as KEI killed our use there. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
It isn't false, because no other class can improve the minds of their ALLIES. Most of the other classes have SELF only mana regen, and those that are group spells, aren't a match for an Enchanter of the same level, except for a bard, and even those are purely mana regen, not adding to mana pool, or other mental enhancements.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Quote:
