<br />

<br />
I think that marking certain mobs as unmezzable is a reasonable thing. This allows them to put a challenge back into an encounter that could be trivialized with mez. You need to create some different tactics for these encounters. And also, these are well known creatures. And you will learn quickly what things can and can't be mezzed.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Quote:
