<br />

<br />
Now, this is the one that really made me reply. There are a LOT of enchanters that use charm in as many situations as they can. I don't consider an LDoN hard adventure as a carefully controlled situation, and yet, many of the enchanters here in The Runes do this. It definately isn't just a backup for unmezzable mobs.
<br />
Yes, they keep nerfing charm. But, come on. When you can charm a mob that hits for 1300+ and "easily" kill things that take a full group, it may be a bit powerful. But, the risk is also there, that many of the non-charmers don't see. All they see is us controlling a huge hitting mob.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Anyway, I still see the description of the Enchanter class as still valid, even though the game has grown and evolved in the years that I have been playing.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://mysite.verizon.net/vze1zkvq/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/gewylsig.jpg" border="0" />
