                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Illusions - all illusions - used to have a faction modifying effect. Some, such as minor illusion - would make you indifferent to many KOS mobs - such as brownies in LFay. The non-racial enchanter illusions were nerfed so that they no longer change your faction. You retain your racial faction. Racial illusions retain the effect of changing your base faction to that of the race you're illusioning to.
<br />

<br />
edit: and as to the comment 'now several racial illusions are insanely hard to obtain' - I only know of two that would qualify, Guktan and Vah Shir, and they were never *easy* to obtain and Guktan is a recent addition. In fact Vah Shir is now so accessable that there are many copies for sale in the bazaar and they sell so slowly that it doesn't pay to make them. Am I misinformed about any other racial illusions that are now 'insanely hard to obtain'?
<br />

<br />
Oh, and I agree that Guktan is insanely hard to obtain - stupidly so. Plus  the nerfs they made to zones so that it couldn't be soloed by 65 enchanters with DC is majorly annoying.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Max
