We didn't lose our sense of faction because of the change.  Your guild seriously asked you if Earth Elementals were KoS in Freeport?  The game shifted focus away from racial factions.  The illusion change didn't.  Racial illusions still modify factions.  Do I wish racial factions still mattered?  In a way, yes.  But the racial factions have nothing to do with the non-racial illusions.  No, that stayed the same.  What changed is that I can cast NDT outside my group, on my pet, because unlike when BotG was new, people can't kill others with it anymore.  What changed is that I can go scaled wolf and benefit from it's speed increase inside cities.  But my faction still matters, because all those forms use my base gnome faction.
<br />

