I've got to disagree on the right of passage bit either.  I went earth elemental, conned, then went in and bought them.  If I hadn't done that, I'd have asked a druid for a wolf form.  Going into Neriak or Qeynos for the 44 tash coins, that was scary.  Exploring Oggok, same thing.  KoS to half the stuff even with illusion, relying on an invis that could drop at any time.  A big area and going LD would mean coming back without my illusion, KoS to the whole zone.  These areas were scary.  These faction impacts are still there.
<br />

<br />
What we did lose was the ability to get non-KoS in velkators using WW.  The ability to get non-KoS in Sol A as a fire elemental (we actually lost that earlier, pre-change though).  The benefits of Earth Elemental in the Hole, as long as you didn't kill much there.  And that one supposedly just a cast of Collaboration will accomplish now.
