                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I believe that Enchanters are the most nerfed class in EQ, although necros were the first to receive the 'large' nerfs , live, we have been battered more times and harder.
<br />

<br />
The fact that our haste is basically a +atk buff rather then uhh... HASTE, is an insult.
<br />

<br />
The fact that our mana regen is just a drop in the bucket compared to bard mana regen song... 
<br />

<br />
The fact that Shamans are now the 'true' masters of illusions with the ability to bestow upon others the ability to chose what illusion , when and where to change into anything that they want(racial) destroyed Enchanters in that area, to make matters worse, save for illusion fire elemental and sometimes werewolf, project illusion was turned into something useless.
<br />

<br />
The fact that Enchanters are the only class who has dots that haven't scaled up with the mobs , although Enchanters are not a dot class, we have dots, which eventually become 100% useless, combining all 3 dots ends up in less then half of the DPS of *1* necro/shaman dot, which are harder to resist .
<br />

<br />
The fact that bards received an AA that was rightfully ours(Fading memories) is a horrid injustice, it should at least be named 'Quick song of the forgotten' or something along those lines so it doesn't intrude on Enchanter territory.
<br />

<br />
The fact that Enchanters have lost the tittle of masters of crowd control(bards) is a big hit.
<br />

<br />
The fact that Enchanters have lost the ability to add charm to the mix slowly and slowly expansion after expansion... shows lack of ... planning from the devs.
<br />

<br />
This can all be fixed by nerfing Bards and Shamans.
<br />

<br />
Whoever said that shamans were nerfed and underpowered should crawl out of the hole they have been living in for the past few expansions.
<br />

<br />
*phew* Well , that is all.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
