                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Absolutely true.... We've been nerfed and forgotten about in expansions to the point where we are mariginal in my opinion.  Unless of course when you count the tells for crack or haste.  
<br />

<br />
Today I am considering changing my main from a 65 enchanter I have played for some 150+ days, since before RoK to another toon that until now has been a diversion or even start one from scratch or....play another game all together.  Today the need for CC is near ZERO, the ability for an enc to add DPS is marginal at best and anything else I can cast you can buy in PoK for a few PP.  Charming is the only real outlet left and that has a bullseye painted all over it.  
<br />

<br />
The devs that created the game are long gone and I believe the current team either A) Does not game, B) Does not play this class or C) lacks the creativity and imagination to design a well balanced, challenging, entertaining game.  The days of "give mobs more HP and DPS slap a new sticker on it and call it an expansion... there that is more challenging" are here.  Even the zone names lack creativity....Tipt?  Where is Qwerty I wonder?  How long they stay will depend on Sony.....  For now let me say, I'd rather have VI and "the vision(tm)".
<br />

<br />
And I am sorry Mr. Brenlo, don't feel like a punching bag.  I feel this way becuase my involvement with EQ has been that way lately.  In the end what will matter is what I do with my hard earned $$.
