                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">So, you're saying groups don't need slow?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I'm saying 65% slow is good enough most of the time.  For that matter, 50% is good enough most of the time.  And when it is good enough, the BL blows the shaman away because the BL boosts mana regen and packs more DPS.
<br />

<br />
It is the thing that hits all specialists.  When we are needed, nobody else can do what we do.  When we are not, the more well rounded classes bring considerably more to the table.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">beastlords can't really do much aside from DPS,</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
You need to get to know some better BLs.  A BL can offtank multiple mobs at once.  He's got paragon.  He boosts mana regen for the whole group.  His slow casts very fast.  He's got most of a shaman's buffing ability.  What's a shaman bring?  75% slow instead of 65%, or 29% less damage the mob does and malo, the ability to land slow easily without aggro worries.  But when your healer has no worries about that, who cares?  Killing more gets you more xp.
<br />

<br />
In the end, DPS stacks.  Everything else is finite.
<br />

<br />
Seriously, think over the shaman class.  You'll see all the things we can complain about, so can they.  And if you read their boards, they do.  You see cannibilize, they see spells with raised mana costs due to their mana regen.  You see vicious dots, they see mobs that are dead long before the dot becomes efficient.  You see 75% slow, they see BLs with a fast casting 65% slow, mana regen, and high DPS.  And then try looking over our class as if you were not an enchanter.  Second best slow, everyone wants slow.  Arcane Rune.  Eldritch Rune.  CoD.  Mez.  Mana regen buffs that everyone wants.  The best haste spell in the game (never mind that bards can stack 2 and exceed us).  Root, improved invisibility.  Dire Charm.  Gather Mana.  The fun of illusions.  Improved Invisibility.
<br />

<br />
You look at us from an outsider view and we are sitting pretty.  From inside the class?  Lack of real crowds to control means we can be bored.  That same lack means bards can do it.  Our escape from that boredom, charming, is frequently limited.  But when you look at another class, unless they are really screwed, you see what they can do that you cannot or what they do that's good enough + everything else they can do better than you.
<br />

<br />
The grass is always greener on the other side of the fence.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
