                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">OH.... I wouldn't say that we "have lost the tittle of masters of crowd control."
<br />

<br />
I still have no problems finding groups, I still haven't seen a bard save a group from a large pull, and I still haven't seen a class that can do so much with so little, it seems.
<br />

<br />
If you time the death of the mobs from 100% to death, then cast Asphyxiate and Cripple on the next and time it, I think you'll find that although you don't apply DPS the way other classes can... you can still seriously help the DPS indirectly.  Also, we do have a marginal nuke that hits for around 1300 with nuke item.
<br />

<br />
I'll agree that we've been the 3rd most neglected class and most nerfed.  If SoE addresses melee issues first, then I'll patiently wait for something like Delegate Main Assist and Mark NPC.
<br />

<br />
OH, we already got those... so I guess SoE did throw us a bone.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
