                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Your "role" is what you make it, others might see it differently but thats their problem.
<br />

<br />
As to the monks being the biggest nerfed out there, nope. They got 1 massive hit a while back but since then it has been slowly reversed till its fairly close to what it used to be. A lot of small changes/nerfs to the Enchanter class (and not just us) however have had no reverse let alone an explanation. Isn't 15x1 > (1x10)-7. Stick a +35 due to the melee changes yet all the casters got exactly what?
<br />

<br />
----------------
<br />
Beta- Aka The Vision.
<br />

<br />
Chanters were supposed to be able to "enchant" stuff and make it better and umm... stuff (it never went fully live).
<br />

<br />
Mezz was ment as a means of escape, not crowd control.
<br />

<br />
Bards originally had the mana regen.
<br />
----------------
<br />

<br />
Kinda left us with charming. Mobs these days are such hard hitters that charming is rather unbalancing, so we are being moved from that arena. (I can charm a mob that tripples for 1300, dangerous to me but others dont see that side)
<br />

<br />
So i think our role is definatly in the bazaar buffing folk for donations. Especially as the NPCs for that role are still being scripted.
<br />

<br />
After that goes live I think it will be Ham and Cheese Roll or maybe Tuna and Cheese. As long as its with cheese then everything will be balanced!</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
